That’s fine — then skip the Python streamer on the E320.

The best workaround now is:

Use a built-in UHD capture tool on the E320 and pipe it over SSH to the host

This gives you a live host spectrograph without needing:

* GNU Radio on the E320
* Python uhd on the E320
* NumPy on the E320

First, check what UHD capture tool exists on the E320

On the E320, run:

which rx_samples_to_file
which uhd_rx_cfile
find /usr /usr/local -type f \( -name 'rx_samples_to_file' -o -name 'uhd_rx_cfile' \) 2>/dev/null

What I want

If you have rx_samples_to_file, that is the easiest path.

⸻

If rx_samples_to_file exists

1) Create a FIFO on the host

On the host:

rm -f /tmp/e320_iq.pipe
mkfifo /tmp/e320_iq.pipe

2) Start the SSH stream from the E320 into that FIFO

On the host:

ssh root@192.168.10.2 \
'rx_samples_to_file --args "type=e3xx,addr=127.0.0.1" \
 --file /dev/stdout \
 --type short \
 --rate 250000 \
 --freq 100000000 \
 --gain 20 \
 --nsamps 0' > /tmp/e320_iq.pipe

Notes:

* addr=127.0.0.1 is for local UHD on the E320
* --type short gives interleaved int16 IQ, which is easy to ingest on the host
* --nsamps 0 is intended as continuous streaming on many UHD example builds; if your build rejects that, tell me the exact error

3) Build the host GNU Radio spectrograph

Use this flowgraph on the host:

File Source (short) -> Interleaved Short To Complex -> Multiply Const -> QT GUI Frequency Sink
                                                                    \-> QT GUI Waterfall Sink

Block settings

File Source

* File: /tmp/e320_iq.pipe
* Output type: short
* Repeat: No

Interleaved Short To Complex

* Default settings are fine

Multiply Const

* Constant: 1.0 / 32768.0

QT GUI Frequency Sink

* Input: complex
* Sample rate: 250e3
* Center frequency: 100e6

QT GUI Waterfall Sink

* Input: complex
* Sample rate: 250e3
* Center frequency: 100e6

4) Startup order

Usually easiest:

1. start the GNU Radio flowgraph on the host
2. then start the SSH pipe command

If the FIFO blocks, that is normal until the other side opens it.

